<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="82" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[140,1108,166,1214]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[185,312,166,192]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis box="[185,307,166,192]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" reason="1">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Can be easily recognized by its long embolus, starting at position about 5 h and making 1.5 coils (Figs 4.1, 5.1, 6.1); and by the shape of tegular apophysis and epigyne.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="82" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[140,1108,166,1214]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[185,336,272,298]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis box="[185,331,272,298]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" reason="1">Description</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Redescribed in detail by 
<bibRefCitation author="Levy G" box="[635,776,272,299]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" pagination="1 - 31" refId="ref19351" refString="Levy G (2003) Spiders of the families Anyphaenidae, Hahniidae, Ctenidae, Zoridae, and Hersiliidae (Araneae) from Israel. Israel Journal of Zoology 49: 1 - 31." type="journal article" year="2003">Levy (2003)</bibRefCitation>
and Rheims et al. (2004, as 
<taxonomicName box="[140,249,308,333]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simoni">
<emphasis box="[140,249,308,333]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">H. simoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="82" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[140,1108,166,1214]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[185,319,342,368]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis box="[185,314,342,368]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" reason="1">Comments</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
This species was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[665,728,343,369]" name="Spain" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Spain</collectingCountry>
, and later reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[992,1070,343,369]" name="Algeria" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Algeria</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry name="Israel" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Israel</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[230,374,378,404]" name="Burkina Faso" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Burkina Faso</collectingCountry>
. Its 
<typeStatus box="[414,469,378,404]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">types</typeStatus>
appear to be lost (
<bibRefCitation author="Levy G" box="[661,780,378,404]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" pagination="1 - 31" refId="ref19351" refString="Levy G (2003) Spiders of the families Anyphaenidae, Hahniidae, Ctenidae, Zoridae, and Hersiliidae (Araneae) from Israel. Israel Journal of Zoology 49: 1 - 31." type="journal article" year="2003">Levy 2003</bibRefCitation>
). It is very likely that that specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[275,419,413,440]" name="Burkina Faso" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Burkina Faso</collectingCountry>
(males) illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Foord SH &amp; Dippenaar-Schoeman AS" box="[664,1108,413,440]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" pagination="255 - 279" refId="ref18755" refString="Foord SH, Dippenaar-Schoeman AS (2005) A revision of the Afrotropical species of Hersiliola Thorell and Tama Simon with the description of a new genus Tyrotama (Araneae: Hersiliidae). African Entomology 13 (2): 255 - 279." type="journal article" year="2005">Foord and Dippenaar-Schoeman (2005)</bibRefCitation>
are not conspecific with specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[582,657,448,474]" name="Algeria" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Algeria</collectingCountry>
(females). Males from 
<collectingCountry box="[908,1051,448,475]" name="Burkina Faso" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Burkina Faso</collectingCountry>
have their embolus base in another position (at 04 hrs) compared to specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[985,1046,483,509]" name="Spain" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Spain</collectingCountry>
or 
<collectingCountry name="Israel" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Israel</collectingCountry>
(at 05 hrs). African males may belong to 
<taxonomicName authority="Blackwall, 1865" authorityName="Blackwall" authorityYear="1865" box="[617,926,518,545]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="versicolor">
<emphasis box="[617,745,519,545]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">H. versicolor</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Blackwall J" box="[751,926,518,545]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" pagination="80 - 101" refId="ref18041" refString="Blackwall J (1865) Descriptions of recently discovered spiders collected in the Cape de Verde Islands by John Gray, Esq. Annals and Magazine of Natural History (3) 16: 80 - 101." type="journal article" year="1865">Blackwall, 1865</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a species known from 
<collectingCountry box="[203,330,554,580]" name="Cape Verde" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Cape Verde</collectingCountry>
from females only. Another possibility is that specimen from 
<collectingCountry name="Burkina Faso" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Burkina Faso</collectingCountry>
had a partially expanded bulbus, and its tegulum was slightly displaced (turned).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[140,1108,166,1214]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">
Figures of “ 
<taxonomicName authority="&quot; in Rheims and Brescovit (2004)" authorityName="&quot; in Rheims and Brescovit" authorityYear="2004" box="[318,813,624,650]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simoni">
<emphasis box="[318,428,625,650]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">H. simoni</emphasis>
” in Rheims and Brescovit (2004)
</taxonomicName>
and Rheims et al. (2004) undoubtedly correspond to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dufour" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[456,622,659,685]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macullulata">
<emphasis box="[456,622,659,685]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">H. macullulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="82" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[140,1108,166,1214]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[185,344,694,720]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis box="[185,339,694,720]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" reason="1">Distribution</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dufour" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[353,520,695,721]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macullulata">
<emphasis box="[353,520,695,721]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">H. macullulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is confirmed here from 
<collectingCountry box="[801,867,695,721]" name="Spain" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Spain</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[881,964,695,721]" name="Algeria" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Algeria</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[977,1036,695,721]" name="Israel" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Israel</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Levy G" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" pagination="1 - 31" refId="ref19351" refString="Levy G (2003) Spiders of the families Anyphaenidae, Hahniidae, Ctenidae, Zoridae, and Hersiliidae (Araneae) from Israel. Israel Journal of Zoology 49: 1 - 31." type="journal article" year="2003">Levy 2003</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Foord SH &amp; Dippenaar-Schoeman AS" box="[217,669,730,757]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" pagination="255 - 279" refId="ref18755" refString="Foord SH, Dippenaar-Schoeman AS (2005) A revision of the Afrotropical species of Hersiliola Thorell and Tama Simon with the description of a new genus Tyrotama (Araneae: Hersiliidae). African Entomology 13 (2): 255 - 279." type="journal article" year="2005">Foord and Dippenaar-Schoeman 2005</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[693,769,730,756]" name="Yemen" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Yemen</collectingCountry>
(as 
<taxonomicName authority=", Rheims et al. 2004" authorityName="Rheims" authorityYear="2004" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simoni">
<emphasis box="[821,934,731,756]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">H. simoni</emphasis>
, Rheims et al. 2004
</taxonomicName>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[228,291,765,791]" name="Libya" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Libya</collectingCountry>
(first record), and 
<collectingCountry box="[523,576,765,791]" name="Serbia" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Mali</collectingCountry>
(first record). Its records from 
<collectingCountry box="[954,1107,765,792]" name="Burkina Faso" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Burkina Faso</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Foord SH &amp; Dippenaar-Schoeman AS" box="[147,590,800,827]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" pagination="255 - 279" refId="ref18755" refString="Foord SH, Dippenaar-Schoeman AS (2005) A revision of the Afrotropical species of Hersiliola Thorell and Tama Simon with the description of a new genus Tyrotama (Araneae: Hersiliidae). African Entomology 13 (2): 255 - 279." type="journal article" year="2005">Foord and Dippenaar-Schoeman 2005</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[655,734,800,826]" name="Turkey" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Yagmur EA &amp; Kunt KB &amp; YalcIn M" box="[748,969,800,827]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" pagination="62 - 64" refId="ref20341" refString="Yagmur EA, Kunt KB, YalcIn M (2008) The first record of family Hersiliidae from Turkey (Arachnida: Araneae). Serket 11 (2): 62 - 64." type="journal article" year="2008">Yağmur et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
) could refer to another species. All reported Central Asian populations refer to 
<taxonomicName authority="Marusik &amp; Fet, 2009" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Fet" authorityYear="2009" box="[890,1039,835,861]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sternbergsi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[890,1039,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">H. sternbergsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1046,1107,836,862]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<collectingCountry box="[147,309,871,898]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
) or 
<taxonomicName authority="Marusik &amp; Fet, 2009" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Fet" authorityYear="2009" box="[355,562,871,897]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Deltshevia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gromovi" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[355,562,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Deltshevia gromovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[569,646,871,897]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
sp. n. (
<collectingCountry box="[730,867,871,898]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[140,1108,166,1214]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[185,249,906,932]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis box="[185,244,906,932]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" reason="1">Note</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
This name has been commonly listed as “ 
<taxonomicName box="[699,832,906,932]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis box="[699,832,906,932]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">H. maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” although Dufour’s original name is 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnæus, 1758" authorityName="Dufour" authorityYear="1831" box="[279,488,941,967]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Aranea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macullulata">
<emphasis box="[279,488,941,967]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Aranea macullulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The name was misspelled as “ 
<taxonomicName box="[826,982,941,967]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macululata">
<emphasis box="[826,982,941,967]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">H. macululata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” by 
<bibRefCitation author="Simon E" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" pagination="1 - 55" refId="ref20006" refString="Simon E (1885) Etudes sur les Arachnides recuellis en Tunisie en 1883 et 1884 par MM. A. Letourneux, M. Sedillot et Valery Mayet, membres de la mission de l'Exploration scientifique de la Tunisie. In: Exploration scientifique de la Tunisie. Paris, 1 - 55." type="book chapter" year="1885">Simon (1885: 28)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Karsch F" box="[272,459,976,1003]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" pagination="1 - 14" refId="ref19013" refString="Karsch F (1881) Verzeichniss der wahrend der Rohlfs'schen Afrikanischen Expedition erbeuteten Myriopoden und Arachniden. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte 47: 1 - 14." type="journal article" year="1881">Karsch (1881: 7)</bibRefCitation>
‘corrected’ the name to “ 
<taxonomicName box="[735,833,976,1002]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis box="[735,833,976,1002]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” which was widely used. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bonnet P" box="[140,372,1011,1038]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" pagination="1926 - 3026" refId="ref18079" refString="Bonnet P (1957) Bibliographia Araneorum. Toulouse, Doladure 2 (3): 1926 - 3026." type="journal article" year="1957">Bonnet (1957: 2180</bibRefCitation>
; footnote) suggested that 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnæus, 1758" authorityName="Dufour" authorityYear="1831" box="[663,789,1011,1037]" class="Insecta" family="Blaberidae" genus="Aranea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macullulata">
<emphasis box="[663,789,1011,1037]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">macullulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is poor Latin, being derived from a non-existent word “macullula” (“a small spot”). The consistent usage for over 100 years still does not validate Karsch’s emendation (ICZN Article 32b-c). In fact, Dufour’s original description (1831: 360) shows that his intention was to document a pattern of very small spots; and “macullula” is acceptable as an invented Latin word, parallel to the existing terms “medullula” or “ampullula” (H.D. Cameron, pers. comm. 1995).
</paragraph>
